Preheat lightly greased barbecue grill to medium-high Season salmon with salt and hot pepper flakes. Drizzle with lime juice and olive oil. Place salmon on grill, flesh side down, for 6 to 8 minutes. Turn fillets and grill for 2 to 4 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Place bread slices on a work surface. Arrange salmon over top. Serve open-faced and top with Peach Salsa.